article.description: Drew Neitzel scored 22 points to lead the No. 25 Spartans to a 76-64 triumph over Wisconsin-Green Bay.
article.headline: Neitzel keeps No. 25 Michigan State perfect at home
article.linkText: Neitzel keeps No. 25 Michigan State perfect at home
article.story: EAST LANSING, Mich. (AP) -- Drew Neitzel scored 22 points and Goran Suton had 14 points, 15 rebounds and five assists in Michigan State's 76-64 win over Wisconsin-Green Bay on Saturday. Neitzel hit four 3-point shots and made it four straight games with at least 20 points for the balanced Spartans (12-2). Suton had a career high in rebounds and matched his top assist total as Michigan State shot 51.8 percent from the field and won its sixth straight game. Travis Walton had 11 points and eight assists, Isaiah Dahlman had 10 points and Marquise Gray contributed nine points and eight rebounds for the Spartans. Mike Schachtner scored 14 points and Ryan Evanochko added 11 for the Phoenix (5-6), who came within a point of the highest total for a Michigan State opponent this season. The Spartans led 36-28 at halftime and survived a scare in the second half before building a 15-point lead in the last two minutes. Michigan State had a 32-24 edge on the boards and cleaned up its ballhandling with 21 assists and just seven turnovers.
